{
  "texts": [
    "The prototypes were tested on three varieties of testing data (20%, 25%, and 40% of whole datasets).",
    "ResNet-50 proved to provide the most reliable performance for accuracy, sensitivity, and specificity over ResNet-18 for the three kinds of testing data.",
    "The best performance value on 20% and 25% test sets achieved a classification accuracy of above 80%, a sensitivity of above 87%, and a specificity of above 83%.",
    "for the three test assortments.",
    "The authors in 42 selected an optimizer and modified the parameters of the CNN models which improved the classification accuracy as they suggested."
  ]
}